# Frontend Architecture Rule (Vue3 + Vite + Pinia + Ant Design Vue)

- Keep layering clear: `views` for pages, `components` for reusable UI, `api` for request wrappers, `stores` for global state, `utils` for pure helpers.
- Do not call `axios` directly in views/components; all HTTP requests must go through `src/api/*` and `src/utils/request.ts`.
- Route meta must stay consistent (`title`, `showInMenu`, `requiresAuth`, `role`, `activeMenu`) and new pages should be lazy-loaded in `src/router/index.ts`.
- Auth state source of truth is store + token storage strategy; avoid scattered `localStorage` reads/writes in multiple pages.
- Vue SFCs must use `script setup lang="ts"` and TypeScript types for API data/contracts.
- Business logic should be extracted from large pages into composables or `api` modules; keep page files focused on UI orchestration.
- Use Ant Design Vue components consistently; avoid mixing ad-hoc UI patterns across pages.
- Reuse shared enums/types/constants instead of hard-coded strings in routes, role checks, and status rendering.
- Error handling and user feedback must be explicit (`message.error/success`) and API failures should be surfaced with actionable text.
- Any new environment variable must be documented in `frontend/env.example`.

## Example

```ts
// ✅ Good: page delegates data access to api layer
const list = await goodsApi.getGoodsList(params)
```
